The Niger state Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has disclosed that four people died in five road traffic crashes during the Sallah holidays. In an interim report for Sallah holiday operations signed by the Corps Sector Commander, Joel Dagwa, 35 people were involved out of which 14 were injured. The report revealed that 15 vehicles were booked for contravening various traffic offences while one vehicle was booked for overloading.